 "description": "Normal men under super-normal leaders. Per 30 bandits rides one 4th-level Fighting-Man; per 50, additionally a 5th- or 6th-level fighter (d6 1-3/4-6); per 100, additionally an 8th- or 9th-level fighter (d6 1-3/4-6). Above 200 bandits there is a 50% chance of a Magic-User (d6 1-4: 10th, 5-6: 11th level) and 25% of an 8th-level Cleric; at exactly 300 the Magic-User is certain and the Cleric chance rises to 50%. Each leader has a 5% chance per level of magical gear, rolled by class: fighters for Armor, Shield, Sword; Magic-Users for Wand/Staff, Ring, Miscellaneous Magic; Clerics for Miscellaneous Weapon, Armor, Shield. Force composition: Light Foot (leather & shield) 40%, Short Bow or Light Crossbow (leather) 25%, Light Horse (leather & shield) 25%, Medium Horse (chain & shield) 10%; leaders ride heavy barded horses. Hit Dice: 1 per man.",
